<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="511" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1787,1993]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1787,1813]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[328,549,1787,1814]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" pagination="445 - 470" refId="ref10667" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. res. (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 445 - 470. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[407,457,1787,1813]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">et al</emphasis>
. (2020)
</bibRefCitation>
. Characteristic added here: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[860,1038,1787,1813]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Dorsal surface with spot extending about ¼ of the length of the pygophore (9A— 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[691,930,1823,1850]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" pagination="445 - 470" refId="ref10667" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. res. (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 445 - 470. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[774,826,1823,1849]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">et al</emphasis>
. (2020))
</bibRefCitation>
. Inner wall with well-swollen area attached to dorsal rim (
<figureCitation box="[325,418,1859,1885]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[250,1339,204,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[199,1389,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genital capsule in posterolateral view, swollen area on inner wall of the pygophore indicated by the arrow: A—Hypoxys triangularis; B—H. capito; C—H. subrastratus; D—H. myrtacivorus sp. n.; E—H. curvatus sp. n.; F—H. striatus sp. n. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911526/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
, black arrow). 
<taxonomicName box="[602,688,1859,1885]" class="Pezizomycetes" family="Helvellaceae" genus="Phallus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pezizales" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[602,688,1859,1885]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Phallus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[708,803,1859,1885]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1114,1138]" captionTargetBox="[179,1370,196,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-25@12.[160,1427,181,1090]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Phallus A—H. triangularis; B—H. subrastratus; C—Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n. Acronyms: ph—phallotheca; vs—vesica. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911522" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911522/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Vesica tapering dorsally in lateral view. Phallotheca curved. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[241,445,1895,1921]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Pars intermedialis subcylindrical medially (
<figureCitation box="[940,1030,1895,1921]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[229,1359,182,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[228,1359,181,1800]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Internal female genitalia: A—Hypoxys trabeculus (Breddin, 1907) (H. quadridens group); B—H. oxyacanthus (Breddin, 1904) (H. oxyacanthus group); C—H. aspilogaster Mendonça et al., 2021 (H. balteatus group); D—H. triangularis (H. triangularis group); E—H. subrastratus (H. triangularis group); F—H. myrtacivorus sp. n. (H. triangularis group). Acronyms: aac—anterior annular crest; ch—chitinellipsen; cs—capsula seminalis; de—ductus receptaculi; vf9—valvifers 9; la9—laterotergite 9; pac—posterior annular crest; pi—pars intermedialis; tvi—thickening of vaginal intima; x—abdominal segment X. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911520/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
). Capsula seminalis with three thick projections: one projection half the length of the others, the other two projections with half of the length of pars intermedialis (
<figureCitation box="[313,403,1967,1993]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[229,1359,182,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[228,1359,181,1800]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Internal female genitalia: A—Hypoxys trabeculus (Breddin, 1907) (H. quadridens group); B—H. oxyacanthus (Breddin, 1904) (H. oxyacanthus group); C—H. aspilogaster Mendonça et al., 2021 (H. balteatus group); D—H. triangularis (H. triangularis group); E—H. subrastratus (H. triangularis group); F—H. myrtacivorus sp. n. (H. triangularis group). Acronyms: aac—anterior annular crest; ch—chitinellipsen; cs—capsula seminalis; de—ductus receptaculi; vf9—valvifers 9; la9—laterotergite 9; pac—posterior annular crest; pi—pars intermedialis; tvi—thickening of vaginal intima; x—abdominal segment X. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911520/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
